# Agent Reminders

These reminders capture reusable lessons. Project-specific additions belong in
this file after installation.

## Domain before UI

Work in this order:

```text
Domain -> Workflow -> State -> Architecture -> Components -> Visual UI
```

Do not solve architectural problems with presentation code.

## Architectural integrity

Before introducing an abstraction, ask:

1. Does it solve a real current problem?
2. Will it have at least two real consumers or enforce a required boundary?
3. Does it reduce coupling?
4. Does it reduce cognitive complexity?
5. Is it documented in SDP?

Otherwise prefer small duplication over premature abstraction.

## State ownership

Each state has one owner: persisted domain state, derived state, shared
interaction state, or local transient UI state. Duplicate ownership is a design
smell.

## Refactoring

Refactor by behavior-preserving vertical slices. Do not split files merely to
reduce line count. Move behavior behind explicit contracts, verify it, then
remove compatibility adapters.

## Roles

The shell owns composition. Workspaces own workflows. Components own rendering.
Services own provider interaction. Domain contracts should not depend on UI
labels or component shapes.

## Evidence

External data is evidence, not automatically truth or prediction. Preserve
source, version, units, no-data semantics and provenance.

## Stop

When the assigned Slice is complete, stop. Record discoveries as future work;
do not continue automatically.
